
				                 In a terse statement the Presidency on Monday said: “The Minister of International Relations and Cooperation, Ms Maite Nkoana-Mashabane will represent President Jacob Zuma at the inauguration ceremony of the President-elect of the Republic of Kenya, His Excellency Mr Uhuru Kenyatta.”
The statement did not give reasons why Zuma was not attending the inauguration scheduled to take place at the Kasarani National Stadium, in Nairobi, Kenya.
– African News Agency (ANA)
